title: 00923 PM_SLP_S5_L missing
message:
Hello, I have a 820-00923 that is missing PM_SLP_S5_L. No liquid damage, client stated just died on him one day. I am thinking dead PCH, would like a second opinion, or something else to check before I call it.

20v at about 70mA


Measurements:
[B]PPBUS: 13v1 
PP5v_S5: 5v 
PP3v3_S5: 
3v3 S5_PWRGD: 3v3 
PP3V3_SUS: 3v3 
PM_SLP_SUS_L: 3v3 
RTC_RESET_L: 3v1 
PCH_SRTCRST_L: 3v1 
PCH_INTRUDER_L: 1v6 
PPDCPRTC_PCH: 1v7 
PM_DSW_PWRGD: 3v4 
PM_SLP_S5_L: 0v (not short)

PM_PWRBTL: 3v3, when shorting SMC ONOFF it drops down to less than a volt[/B]

title: 00923 PM_SLP_S5_L missing
message:
[B]"PCH_INTRUDER_L: 1v6[/B]"
Check R1401.
If good, try forcing 100K instead of 1M.
